<p><b>Peripeteia</b> (<a href="/wiki/Greek_language" title="Greek language">Greek</a>, <span lang="grc" xml:lang="grc">Περιπέτεια</span>) is a reversal of circumstances, or turning point. The term is primarily used with reference to works of literature. The English form of peripeteia is <i>peripety</i>. Peripety is a sudden reversal dependent on intellect and logic. In <a href="/wiki/Modern_Greek" title="Modern Greek">modern Greek</a> <i>περιπέτεια</i> means <a href="/wiki/Adventure" title="Adventure">adventure</a>.</p>
